BEGIN_PGML

[@ image( "UBC-DYN-17-017.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

A slider block with negligible mass is connected to a uniform rod with a mass of [`5`] [`kg`]. If [`F=20`] [`N`] of force is applied to the block in the direction of the guide, calculate the acceleration of the slider when it starts to move from rest. Assume the coefficient of kinetic friction between the slider block and the guide is [`0.3`] and the guide is oriented [`\theta=[$theta]^{\circ}`] above the horizontal.

[`a=`] [______]{"$a"} [`m/s^2`]

